The paper introduces an extension of Answer Set Programming to reason with preferences, which is a topic commonly studied in the field of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the complexity of the problem of finding preferred stable models, which is related to logic and computation (cs.LO). The use of set constraint programming and optimization techniques suggests that the paper may also be relevant to programming languages and compilers (cs.PL), as well as data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
